\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Per-method calibration against the cross-validation ground truth on D1 (six real miners; each point is one miner, dashed line $y{=}x$). The generative and resampling metrics (v1, v2.6-mle, Bootstrap) sit on the line; PM4Py forms a flat high band that ignores the ground-truth gradient: it rates the pathological Alpha model (at R1$\approx 0.27$) as $0.91$; AVATAR and SpeciAL scatter off the line. Reading the vertical axis alone, a metric that spreads its six miners discriminates between them, whereas PM4Py compresses them into a narrow band.}}{19}{figure.1.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:calibration}{{4}{19}{Per-method calibration against the cross-validation ground truth on D1 (six real miners; each point is one miner, dashed line $y{=}x$). The generative and resampling metrics (v1, v2.6-mle, Bootstrap) sit on the line; PM4Py forms a flat high band that ignores the ground-truth gradient: it rates the pathological Alpha model (at R1$\approx 0.27$) as $0.91$; AVATAR and SpeciAL scatter off the line. Reading the vertical axis alone, a metric that spreads its six miners discriminates between them, whereas PM4Py compresses them into a narrow band}{figure.1.4}{}}
