\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Speed against accuracy on D1: time per model (log scale) versus mean absolute error to R1; lower-left is better. PM4Py is fast but inaccurate, AVATAR is both slow and inaccurate, while ShadowGen and bootstrap sit at low error and interactive speed. R1 (the ground truth) costs about two minutes and cannot score a model in hand; anti-alignments (M4) and pattern-based (M8) return no score at all (Sect.\nobreakspace  {}\ref {sec:eval:feasibility}).}}{23}{figure.1.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:pareto}{{6}{23}{Speed against accuracy on D1: time per model (log scale) versus mean absolute error to R1; lower-left is better. PM4Py is fast but inaccurate, AVATAR is both slow and inaccurate, while ShadowGen and bootstrap sit at low error and interactive speed. R1 (the ground truth) costs about two minutes and cannot score a model in hand; anti-alignments (M4) and pattern-based (M8) return no score at all (Sect.~\ref {sec:eval:feasibility})}{figure.1.6}{}}
